This paper deals with the determinization of Büchi automata, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of history trees and Rabin automata, which are commonly used in the study of formal languages and automata theory, making cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions deterministic automata and parity acceptance condition, which are topics in computer science theory and algorithms, suggesting cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as a possible sub-category. The use of ordered trees and the mention of index complexity may also indicate cs.PL (Programming Languages) as a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the study of automata with a specific acceptance condition, which may fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
